[[File:Holmestrand komm.svg|thumb]] The '''coat of arms of [[Holmestrand]]''' was approved by Royal Resolution on 14 November 1898.<ref name="kommune.no">{{cite web|url=http://www.holmestrand.kommune.no/Artikkel.aspx?AId=708&back=1&MId1=45&MId2=&MId3=&|title=Kommunevåpen|publisher=Holmestrand kommune|accessdate=2012-02-19|language=no|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120804234008/http://www.holmestrand.kommune.no/Artikkel.aspx?AId=708&back=1&MId1=45&MId2=&MId3=&|archivedate=2012-08-04|df=}}</ref> It was created by the artist Andreas Bloch (1860-1917).<ref name="kommune.no"/> It among other things points to the towns connections with the naval hero [[Peter Tordenskjold]] (in the middle of the white eagle is a picture of his ship ''Hvide Ørn'' 'white eagle').<ref name="kommune.no"/> The official version of the coat of arms also features a golden [[mural crown]] with three towers.<ref name="kommune.no"/>
==Blasoning== Norwegian: ''På rød bunn en sølv, flakt ørn som i høyre klo holder et gull anker og i venstre en gull æskulapstav. I blått hjerteskjold en sølv fregatt.''
