{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}} {{Infobox Radio station |name = Radio Lagos |image = |city = [[Lagos]] |area = [[Lagos State]] |frequency = 107.5 [[Megahertz|MHz]] [[FM broadcasting|FM]] |airdate = |format = |language = Mixed [[Indigenous language|indigenous]] and English |power = |coordinates = {{Coord|6|37|10.767|N|3|21|12.719|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |owner = [[Lagos State|Lagos State Radio Corporation]] |website = }}
'''Radio Lagos 107.5 FM''' (also known as Tiwa n' Tiwa) began operations in 1977 as an offshoot of the Nigerian Broadcasting Corporation. It is the first [[state-owned]] [[Frequency modulation|FM]] [[List of radio stations in Lagos|radio station]] in [[Lagos State]]
The station originally operated on two A.M. Frequencies (990&nbsp;kHz.303mtrs and 918&nbsp;kHz.327mtrs). The need for transformation produced Radio Lagos 107.5 FM (Tiwa n'Tiwa) under the control of the Lagos State Radio Service in 2001.
Radio Lagos is the first predominantly specialized, language station with over 98% of its transmission in [[Yoruba language|Yoruba]] and Egun, and approximately 2% for [[English language|English]] bulletins. The station target audience includes Yoruba speaking listeners in [[Lagos]] and [[Nigerian diaspora]].<ref>{{cite web|website=RadioAfrican|title=Radio Lagos 107.5 Online|author=Haris Aslam|date=20 November 2014|url=http://www.radioafrican.com/radio-lagos-107-5-fm-online/}}</ref>
